ll mushkilāt al-Shudhūr, along with an Arabic-English glossary of its alchemical terminology.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Arabic.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAlchemie. 4aMittelalter. 4aPoesie. 4aSyrien. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Koran & Sacred Writings.2bisacsh  aAlchemy.  aMiddle Ages.  aPoetry.  aSyria.1 aMüller, Juliane , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311077928840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311077935640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110779356423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110779356/original  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023